CatDescriptText: Cutline of image of James Edward Washington, published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, pg. B14 reads: "Win Contest - These two young people won the annual Scholarship Contest sponsored by the Education committee of Deborah Grand Chapter, OES, in Schenley High School., and right, James Edward Washington of Donora, won the music contest. Both winners received a scholarship valued at $200. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."Cutline of image of Andrew Hughey and Vernon Pressley Jr., published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, pg. B15 reads: "Runners-Up - Andrew Hughey of Pittsburgh, left;...and Vernon Pressley Jr. of Clairton, right, were contenders in annual Scholarship Contest sponsored by Deborah Grand Chapter, OES, in Schenley High School.  They received $25 each for their efforts.  A total of $500 was awarded the young people.  Mrs. Iona Howard is state grand chairman of education. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of scholarship winners, from left, James Edward Washington, Vernon Pressley Jr., and Andrew Hughey, posed in front of light colored wall in Schenley High School
